&lt;p&gt;each layer can be described mathematically as below, the process to compute through the layers to the final layer is what we call &lt;strong&gt;forward propagation&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\begin{align}&lt;br /&gt;
\label{eq:3}&lt;br /&gt;
z^{(l)} &amp;amp;= W^{(l)}a^{(l-1)} + b^{(l)} &amp;amp;&amp;amp; (\text{if } l &amp;gt; 1) \\&lt;br /&gt;
a^{(l)} &amp;amp;= \begin{cases}&lt;br /&gt;
\sigma(z^{(l)}) &amp;amp; \text{if } l &amp;gt; 1 \\&lt;br /&gt;
x &amp;amp; \text{if } l = 1&lt;br /&gt;
\end{cases}&lt;br /&gt;
\end{align}&lt;/p&gt;</description><dc:creator>K4i</dc:creator><media:content url="https://k4i.top//images/icons/gradient-descent.png" medium="image"><media:title type="html">featured image</media:title></media:content><category>gradient-descent</category><category>AI</category></item></channel></rss>